On Escalation Ticket # 00420874 the Following Fields have been updated:

On Escalation Ticket # 00420874 the new comment has been added: Yes, here is what I told them to run, they said that they ran it both on the machine in the environment and on a test machine outside of the environment and both resulted in an empty log file.

cd /var/log/epp-client/
touch epp_client_daemon.log
sudo service epp-client-daemon-d restart (if this command fails, change epp-client-daemon-d to epp-client-daemon)

They said that the commands ran properly with no spelling errors. However, on both machines resulted in empty log files.

On Escalation Ticket # 00420874 the new comment has been added: Marius-Viorel Iacob:

@WaitingOnEngineer 
Hello,

I tested EPP of a similar but not exact version and the logging worked as expected. I would please ask the customer to provide their install package for v1.3.1.5 to test locally with their version.

I also have some more tests for them to run:

	 - 	Please provide the output of "journalctl --system"; maybe there is something in the system log about blocking access to the log file
	 - 	I would also suggest a test run of epp-client-daemon with strace to see information about the log file access; please make sure the service is stopped; also check with "ps -aux | grep epp" that epp-client-daemon isn't running; then run "sudo strace /opt/cososys/sbin/epp-client-daemon -e 2>&1 | tee epp-strace"; Ctrl-C after the startup sequence is done; and send the generated "epp-strace" file to us

On Escalation Ticket # 00420874 the new comment has been added: Customer was unable to install 2.4.4.1000, so they asked the customer to install 1.7.0.7 on the impacted machine as they were seeing logging occur on their test machine with this build. Once installed, the customer saw the machine no longer show as offline in the console and they are hoping that this resolved their original issue.

Question that they do have is, is there an alternative method to open the endpoint protector client window on linux? They have found the issue to be intermittent, but sometimes when they right click the EPP icon, the context menu does not appear. They are looking for a workaround in case this does occur to still be able to get to the EPP Client window.

On Escalation Ticket # 00420874 the new comment has been added: Marius-Viorel Iacob:

@WaitingOnEngineer
Hello,
On version 1.7.0.7 there is no alternative way of opening the notifier. Make sure the About dialog window is not open (it prevents the right-click menu from opening). Other than that they could try to kill the notifier and reopen it: pkill epp-client
